// Demonstrates the `wait` keyword — explicit deferred initialization.
//
// `int i = wait;` declares `i` with the promise that an assignment
// will follow before the value is read. The validator enforces the
// promise at compile time; the codegen emits zero-of-type at the
// declaration site and the later assignment overrides it.
//
// This is the explicit-deferred-init form (Candidate D from the
// no-null open question), distinct from `var i : int;` which uses
// the same lowering but no source-level deferral signal.

function int wait_demo() {
    int answer = wait;
    answer = 42;
    return answer;
}

function int main() {
    return wait_demo();
}
